Make the kwargifier work on methods too.

The limitation here is that only existing methods can be used (eg. x = kwargify(y.z)) because if we wanted to decorate function to become a kwargified method, the kwarigfy class would have to be a descriptor.

Pythonification

- No longer a stateless class
- Implements __wrapped__
- Doesn't impersonate another object by abusing properties
  (If you want access to the wrapped function, use __wrapped__)
- Can wrap methods as well as functions
